1st row<p>Take our signature tour, and let Central Park Conservancy guides give you an insider&#39;s look at some of the most iconic features of the world&#39;s greatest urban park. Learn how rocky, swampy land was built into the living work of art that is Central Park today.&nbsp;Highlights of this tour include: the Dairy, Sheep Meadow, Cherry Hill, The Lake, Bow Bridge, Bethesda Terrace, The Mall, and Literary Walk.</p><p>Audio enhancement equipment will be used for this tour. A limited number of hearing loops are available and can be requested with ticket purchase.</p><p><strong>Details</strong></p><p><strong>Meet</strong>:&nbsp;Dairy Visitor Center &amp; Gift Shop&nbsp;(mid-Park between 64th and 65th Streets). Enter the Park at 60th Street and Fifth Avenue, and follow the path adjacent to the drive (road) north; the Dairy will be on your left.&nbsp;&nbsp;Please note&nbsp;Google Maps does not recognize this location.<a href="http://assets.centralparknyc.org/images/tours/maps/Dairy_Start_Map.jpg?utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=cpc-engagement&amp;utm_campaign=2018_spring_tours&amp;utm_content=nycparks&amp;s_src=2018_spring_tours&amp;s_subsrc=nycparks">Map of start location</a></p><p><strong>Terrain: </strong>A few inclines and some stairs.</p><p><strong>Length of Tour:</strong> Approximately 90 minutes</p><p><strong>Cost: </strong>Tickets $15 (Members $10). <a href="http://www.centralparknyc.org/events/parent-events/iconic-views-tour.html?utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=cpc-engagement&amp;utm_campaign=2018_spring_tours&amp;utm_content=nycparks&amp;s_src=2018_spring_tours&amp;s_subsrc=nycparks">Purchase tickets online</a>!&nbsp;</p><p>For weather cancellation and other ticket policies, please review our&nbsp;<a href="http://www.centralparknyc.org/tours/tour-faq.html?utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=cpc-engagement&amp;utm_campaign=2018_spring_tours&amp;utm_content=nycparks&amp;s_src=2018_spring_tours&amp;s_subsrc=nycparks">Tours Frequently Asked Questions</a>&nbsp;(FAQ).</p><p>Groups of seven or more must schedule a group tour three weeks in advance at&nbsp;<a href="mailto:tours@centralparknyc.org?subject=Tour%20Inquiry%20from%20NYC%20Parks">tours@centralparknyc.org</a>.</p>
2nd row<p>New York City is home to an amazing abundance of wildlife. Our Urban Park Rangers will guide you to the best wildlife viewing spots in the urban jungle. We offer birding&nbsp;programs throughout the year. Birding programs are appropriate for all skill levels and beginners are welcome.</p><p>To enhance your experience we encourage you to bring binoculars and field guides, or ask a Ranger to borrow a pair.</p>
3rd row<p>Enjoy a Halloween-themed lunch, music and dancing!&nbsp; Recreation Center members are invited to attend.</p><p>For more information, please call (718) 829-0156.</p>
4th row<p><a href="http://moosikikids.com/index.htm">Moosiki Kids Musical Storytime</a> fosters a love of reading at a young age with musical stories and sing-along encouragement on our comfy and danceable turf lawn by the big locomotive.&nbsp;</p><p>This event is great for kids aged 5 years and under! Wear sunscreen or bring shade.&nbsp;</p>
5th row<p>Head to the High Line each Tuesday night for a romantic walk along the park and a chance to take a closer look at the stars. Peer through high-powered telescopes provided by the knowledgeable members of the&nbsp;Amateur Astronomers Association of New York&nbsp;to see rare celestial sights.</p><p>Stargazing at the High Line takes place every Tuesday, beginning at dusk, between Tuesday, April 3, and Tuesday, October 30.</p><p>In the event of rain, Stargazing on the High Line will be cancelled. Check back or follow @highlinenyc on&nbsp;<a href="http://twitter.com/highlinenyc">Twitter</a>&nbsp;for updates every Tuesday by 3pm.</p><p><strong>Partners</strong><br />Stargazing at the High Line is presented by Friends of the High Line in partnership with the&nbsp;Amateur Astronomers Association.</p><p><strong>Support</strong><br />High Line Programs are supported, in part, with public funds from the New York City Council, under the leadership of Speaker Corey Johnson.&nbsp;</p>
